comment.en: Application - Concepts particular to Data Apps, beyond the scope of general resources, that are installed within the infrastructure in order to communicate or process data on behalf of participants of the Copernicus Data Space.

Contract issued by the Data Consumer requesting the usage of a Resource at particular conditions. No privileges are granted to any Party. 

It proposes a Rule over an Resource from an assignee.
A machine-interpretable Data Asset, such as a script file, algorithm, rule set, or another type of code, which execution relies on a particular runtime environment.

The Connector is communication server providing and consuming data by means of Data Apps via a number of resource Endpoints. There are different types of Connectors according to provided capabilities.

Contract issued by the Data Provider offering the usage of a Resource at particular conditions.

It represents Rules that are being offered from an assigner Participant. It does not grant any Rules.

Abstract set of rules governing the usage of a Resource.

A Data Service is an organized system that expose Resources to Participants. It implements a set of operations that allow consumers to access data and applications, and computing and storage resources.
Data Services are all services users aim to use. The access to these services is protected and the relative usage is managed by the policy framework.
Process and result of certifying an interested party in order to become a certified member of the CDS.
It manages and validates the digital identity of CDS Participants

It represents Rules that have been granted from assigner to assignee Participant. Typically used to grant the terms of the Rules between Participants.

The Metadata Broker Service Provider is an intermediary that stores and manages information about the data and data sources available in the ecosystem. Its primary task is receiving and providing metadata, via a dedicated and standard interface (e.g., REST). On-premises installation: A Service Provider deploys the Data App inside of an on-premises CDS Connector on behalf of the Data Provider. This is assumed to be the default case.

On-premises injection: A Service Provider deploys the Data App inside of an on-premises CDS Connector on behalf of the Data Consumer (asking for customized data preprocessing, according to contract specifications; e.g., edge computing).  

Remote integration: A Service Provider integrates a remote Data App service on behalf of the Data Provider. In this scenario, the Data App is hosted by different participants and used remotely.

Possible values:
AND: The relation is satisfied when all of the Constraints are satisfied.

contributor.value:
The Free strategy does not charge the usage of resources. 
The Freemium strategy exposes a limited parts (or capabilities) of the resource at no cost, while additional parts are charged Pay-per-Use, or based on a Flat Rate. 
The Pay-per-Use strategy relies on a particular metrics (volume, access count, download) to define a charged instance of usage.
The Flat Rate strategy charges usage per quantitative slot (time, volume, credit), optionally associated with a tiered cost model according to the configuration of the retrieved resource.
